@pittgoose This ended up requiring a rework of the support code library as proxying the support code in src/index was causing an issue when trying to determine the caller.

Cucumber-js currently complains about ambiguous matches for patterns that cannot apply.

Patterns should only be unique within the Given, When, Then.

e.g. 

    Given bacon is life
     When I eat bacon
     Then bacon is gone

And the following steps:

    defineSupportCode(function({Given, When, Then}) {
      Given('bacon is {\S+}', function(statement) { });
      When('I {\S+} bacon', function(verb) { });
      Then('bacon is {\S+}', function(state) { });
    });

Generates the following error:

    Multiple step definitions match:
      bacon is {S+} - feature\support\step.js:8
      bacon is {S+} - feature\support\step.js:14

It shouldn't matter that I use the same statement in a Given and Then block, because there's no way they can be used like that.

